Class MultipleChoiceQuestion

  • java.lang.Object
    • quest.AbstractQuestion
      • quest.MultipleChoiceQuestion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Question
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MultipleAnswerQuestion

    public class MultipleChoiceQuestion
extends AbstractQuestion
    This class creates multiple choice questions. It allows questions that have multiple choices, allowing the answer to select one of the choices. It will indicate if the input answer matches * the correct answer.

      • inputAnswer

        public java.lang.String inputAnswer(java.lang.String input)
        This method checks the input and determines if it's the correct choice.
        Parameters:
        input - Input the answer to the question. The method will compare the first digit of the input answer, anything else will be ignored. Anything other than the correct answer will be incorrect.
        Returns:
        Returns string correct or incorrect based on the answer input.
